name: Warung Dadi Wahana Bermain Anak
address: F44C+VWM Perumahan Griya Dhadi Idaman, Jl. Jepun No, Dauh Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82111, Indonesia
review 1: It's a great place if you want to bring your kids for a fun mini waterpark experience. There's not really a swimming pool for adult. I think the pool is less than half a meter deep. The food is decent but won't really go here just to eat. It's more for parents and kids.
review 2: Great place to spend time with your kids. Spacious ground with indoor playgroubd in the middle of Balinese village. Price is also very reasonable üëçüëçüëç
review 3: A hidden gem for children attraction around this area.
review 4: It's more like kids play ground, they have water park for kids 5 years old or older.
review 5:
Playground is worth the price. I think the pool is also fine (only kids pool available).

But food should be improved!

name: Porkpoy Ribs Tabanan
address: F44C+XPF, Dauh Peken, Tabanan, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82113, Indonesia
review 1:
Really loved the ambiance here!

Feels like you're eating at someone's house in a very homey way.

The food was amazing. I really love their pork ribs with reasonable prices. Spent around 200k for 4 persons.

My only problem was the setting is basically semi outdoor, so you had to bring your own umbrella if it's raining. Other than that, none. I will definitely come back.
review 2: Food are really good. Staff are friendly. Price affordable. All pork menu. However it can get pretty hot on day time as it has no air condition.
review 3:
Worth the price. Portion was good too. Had the jumbo pork ribs and it was fell off the bone. Service was okay.

They have kids playground but it next door. You CANNOT have what you ordered here and eat by the playground since it's not 'HALAL'. Found it a little bit dissapointing, but glad the server by the playground would watch my kid when i asked her to.

Would recommend this place to others and will definitely come back.
review 4: We were very excited to eat porkpoy, we gone there many times when and ordered gojek allot. However today we learned that they were at a new place. The food however tastes nothing like the old porkpoy. I was actually really disappointed with the taste. The sate babi was very sour and very soft texture, also the bumbu wasn't tasteful like it used to be. Actually nothing tasted like the old porkpy, I used to get really excited eating here but today i left sad and unsatisfied. Sad to see another delicious food ruined.
review 5: Special pork lover ,balinese Chinese, style, good taste

name: Kedai M. Aboe Talib
address: Jl. Gajah Mada No.53, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
What an experience!
The coffee shop is tiny, it is about 2 meter wide, but have 3 stairs full of customer! Been served coffee lover since 1940, runned by 3rd generation of the family.

open daily at 06:00 to 00:00, they kept traditionally way of brewing just as in 1940.

one of the legendary place in Tabanan, that you can‚Äôt miss! my recommendation is Kopi Susu (8K) and Kopi Saring (6K). also they provide tons of delicious jajan pasar, exactly what you want to chew while enjoying coffee.
review 2:
Kopi: Legend!
Service: Excellent!
Atmosphere: Classical Ambience!
Price: Economis!
review 3: The legend coffee shop in Tabanan regency. The best taste for coffee around Tabanan. Inexpensive so you can afford it with well-vibe to share your meeting or your bussiness. Easy to find for locals, but if you are foreign, It's located exactly beside of the Bintang Baru shop and Kawan shop.
review 4: The vibe is great for hanging out and enjoy the coffee. I ordered hot milk and ginger, and it's so great ngl. And this coffee shop is cheap too.
review 5: What a people coffee. Coffee with condensed milk cost 8000 rupiah and black coffee (cloth filtered method) cost 6000 rupiah. Their service is fast. They also has lot of indonesian snacks like banana fritter, fried yam, fried tofu, friend tempeh and many more for 1000 rupiah each. This coffee shop already exist since 1940.

name: Warung DKI
address: Gg. IA No.1, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82113, Indonesia
review 1:
Ok, I need to make more noise for this establishment. Exceptionally underrated in Bali, even within the Balinese community.

For a meat+fried food dish, it is exceptionally clean in taste. Mouth feel isn't oily, flavours aren't overpowering (although sambal is incredibly spicy) the variety of flavours from sweet to savory are a treat to have and portion size is perfect for a meal, unlike other places that over provide.

It's somewhat hard to locate with only one way roads. To make matters worse it is along a remote street. GPS location is correct though! Stop your car outside the main street and walk in.

Definitely recommend this place.
review 2:
The crispy pig skin, and spicy sambal here is great. The food also feels clean and neat.
The portion is Okay, not too much and not too small.
The seats are traditionally on floor, on bali traditional house.
Nice place to visit.
review 3: Best bigul ever! I have few preferences but this one is one of my favorite. Taste is light and a bit different from others. They have small, medium and big portions. The only problem was it is a house typed "warung". A big hard to find. Easy to access by motorcycle.
review 4: Great value for the portions, the pork cracklings is to die for, every component of the meal was so flavourful. You won‚Äôt regret. It‚Äôs in the middle of small alleyway so, you need to really look for the shop sign.
review 5: Delish!! I took the photo after I had the first bite cus I was hungry.

review 1: The fish are fresh. The Sauce also so delicious.

name: Warung Kenanga
address: Jl. Melati No.25, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia

My husband had paket nasi capcay kolobak 28k which was the best he has had since we were in tabanan last year. I had the big portion of paket nasi goreng koloke 28k, cooked to perfection, 10/10! And the staff there couldn't have been more attentive, thank you.

We will certainly return the next time visit in Tabanan city and recommend to others too üåºüí´
review 2: Chinese food is already a rare find so don‚Äôt expect too much. It‚Äôs more of local interpretation of Chinese food.
review 3: Taste is OK but take long time to be serviced
review 4:
Nice local and Chinese food .
Decent price
Decent ambience
The best nasi goteng that I eat in tabanan region of bali island . Owner was taking the order - perfect English ( I think I can learn from her üòÇ) .. funny and interactive.
Recommend !
P.S.
They have another branch in canguu , which I‚Äôm going to visit soon
review 5: My go to place for nasi goreng! It's a typical wok chinese nasi goreng, smoky and sweet. I tried mie goreng, it wasn't that special tbh however other menu is nice as well.

name: Es Waneng
address: Jl. Mawar No.25, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Famous dessert in tabanan. Come in small glass with crushed ice, burned coconut milk, brown sugar syrup and mashed burned candlenut. Really authentic taste. The warung is already open since 1938! Pro tip: take bread behind the seller (cost 1000 rupiah) and mix in glass of es waneng (cost 2000 rupiah).
review 2: Unique ice cream, delicious palm sugar taste must be combined with bread
review 4: This place has a great story behind the waneng ice. Love the taste.
review 5: So and so..too sweet..kind of hard to notice the hidden stall..
